videos.description: Tulsa quarterback Luke Skipper keeps it on a read-option and cuts his way 12 yards into the end zone as the Golden Hurricane take an early 7-0 lead over the Bulls.
videos.headline: Skipper caps first drive with TD

videos.description: USF's Tyre McCants catches a screen pass from Quinton Flowers and breaks through Tulsa tacklers to stay inbounds for the 25-yard score to tie the game at 7-7.
videos.headline: McCants tip-toes in for tying score

videos.description: USF's Darius Tice takes the handoff up the middle and outruns Tulsa's defense for the 54-yard score that gives the Bulls a 14-7 lead.
videos.headline: Tice runs through eye of Golden Hurricane defense for TD

videos.description: USF quarterback Quinton Flowers drops back and throws it deep for Darnell Salomon who beats his defender and catches the pass in the end zone for the 35-yard score.
videos.headline: Flowers airs it out for Salomon

videos.description: USF quarterback Quinton Flowers dances behind his blockers in an attempt to gain more yards on a scramble, but he is hit from behind by Diamon Cannon and Tulsa recovers the fumble.
videos.headline: Flowers fumbles fighting for extra yards

videos.description: USF's Quinton Flowers spins and jukes out of a sack and turns it into a 27-yard first down run.
videos.headline: Flowers shows insane elusiveness on scramble

videos.description: Tulsa's quarterback Luke Skipper scores again on a 9-yard scramble to cut the deficit to 24-17 before half.
videos.headline: Skipper slithers in for second score

videos.description: USF head coach Charlie Strong says that his defense needs to eliminate big plays on third down over the next two quarters against Tulsa.
videos.headline: USF looks to take away the big play in the second half

videos.description: The USF punt return unit has no problem busting through the Tulsa line and blocking the punt to recover deep in Tulsa territory.
videos.headline: Blocked punt puts USF in scoring position

videos.description: USF's Quinton Flowers escapes the pocket but throws across his body and the pass is picked in the end zone by Tulsa's Diamon Cannon.
videos.headline: Flowers throws costly red zone INT

videos.description: Down two scores in the fourth, Tulsa blocks USF's punt and recovers to set up a field goal to make it 27-20.
videos.headline: Blocked punt gives Tulsa life
